# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# pyanchor environment variables
#
# Copy to `.env` (or load via your process manager) before running.
# Most projects only need the 5 REQUIRED entries below. The other 50+
# vars in this file are all OPTIONAL with sensible defaults — you only
# touch them to opt into specific features.
#
# `npx pyanchor init` writes the 5 required entries for you (auto-
# detects framework + agent + paths, generates the token).
#
# This file is organized as:
#   1. REQUIRED (5 entries)        ← the only ones you have to set
#   2. Agent + framework picks     ← change defaults here
#   3. Networking + ports          ← override sidecar bind / proxy paths
#   4. Production gating + auth    ← gate cookie, HMAC actor signing
#   5. Output mode + audit log     ← apply / pr / dryrun + audit JSONL
#   6. PR mode (if output_mode=pr) ← git + gh setup
#   7. Webhooks                    ← Slack / Discord / raw event sinks
#   8. Adapter-specific knobs      ← per-CLI binary paths + tweaks
#
# Section 1 is the MVP. Sections 2-8 are opt-in.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. REQUIRED (5 entries) — the only ones you HAVE to set
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── REQUIRED: target app integration ────────────────────────────────

# Absolute path to your running app (Next.js / Vite / Astro / SvelteKit
# / Remix / anything). Pyanchor rsyncs successful edits here.
PYANCHOR_APP_DIR=/path/to/your/app

# Executable that restarts your Next.js frontend after a successful edit.
# Examples: a script that wraps `pm2 restart`, `systemctl restart`,
# `docker compose restart`, etc. Pyanchor invokes it with no arguments.
PYANCHOR_RESTART_SCRIPT=/path/to/restart-frontend.sh

# URL that should return 2xx once the frontend is back up. Used for
# self-healing after a restart.
PYANCHOR_HEALTHCHECK_URL=http://127.0.0.1:3000/

# ─── REQUIRED: agent workspace ───────────────────────────────────────

# Scratch directory the agent writes into before changes are synced
# back to PYANCHOR_APP_DIR. Should be writable by the agent process.
PYANCHOR_WORKSPACE_DIR=/path/to/pyanchor-workspace


# ─── REQUIRED: bearer token for the runtime + admin API ──────────────

# All /api/* routes and the admin index require this token via either
# `Authorization: Bearer <token>` or `?token=<token>`.
# Generate with: openssl rand -hex 32
PYANCHOR_TOKEN=replace-me-with-32-random-bytes


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. Agent + framework picks — change defaults here
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ─── Agent backend (default: openclaw) ───────────────────────────────

# Which agent adapter handles the AI step.
# Built-in: openclaw (default), claude-code, codex, aider, gemini
# claude-code requires `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk` to be installed.
# codex requires the OpenAI Codex CLI on PATH (`npm i -g @openai/codex`).
# aider requires the aider-chat CLI on PATH (`pip install aider-chat`).
# gemini requires the Google Gemini CLI on PATH (`npm i -g @google/gemini-cli`).
# PYANCHOR_AGENT=openclaw

# Shared agent knobs (used by all adapters where applicable).
# PYANCHOR_AGENT_ID=pyanchor
# Model id format is BACKEND-SPECIFIC. As of v0.32.3 the default is
# EMPTY — when unset, codex / claude-code / aider / gemini each use
# their own CLI default (whatever is in `~/.codex/config.toml`,
# `aider --model` default, etc.) so a single `PYANCHOR_AGENT_MODEL`
# value can't accidentally break a non-openclaw adapter. OpenClaw
# falls back to `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` internally. To override per-
# adapter, set this to the matching backend's model id (e.g.
# `gemini-2.5-pro` for gemini, `o4-mini` for codex, etc.).
# PYANCHOR_AGENT_MODEL=
# PYANCHOR_AGENT_THINKING=medium


# ─── Framework profile (default: nextjs) ─────────────────────────────

# Which framework profile drives default install/build commands,
# rsync excludes, and route hints. Built-in (5 profiles, v0.32.0+):
#   nextjs (default), vite, astro, sveltekit, remix
# Unknown values fall back to nextjs with a warning. For Nuxt or any
# custom stack, leave this as nextjs and override the two commands
# below directly.
# PYANCHOR_FRAMEWORK=nextjs

# Shell command to install workspace dependencies. Empty/unset = use
# the framework profile's default. Runs in PYANCHOR_WORKSPACE_DIR via
# `bash -lc` as the agent user.
#   nextjs default: corepack yarn install --frozen-lockfile
#   vite default:   npm install
# PYANCHOR_INSTALL_COMMAND="pnpm install --frozen-lockfile"

# Shell command to validate the workspace builds before sync-back.
# Empty/unset = use the framework profile's default.
#   nextjs default: env NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1 ./node_modules/.bin/next build
#   vite default:   npm run build
# PYANCHOR_BUILD_COMMAND="pnpm run build"


# ─── Agent: OpenClaw-specific ────────────────────────────────────────

# Path to the OpenClaw CLI binary.
# Default: openclaw (resolved via PATH)
# PYANCHOR_OPENCLAW_BIN=openclaw

# Unix user to invoke OpenClaw as. Defaults to the user running pyanchor.
# Set this if your agent runs under a different account (sudo required).
# PYANCHOR_OPENCLAW_USER=openclaw


# ─── Agent: Codex CLI (PYANCHOR_AGENT=codex) ─────────────────────────

# Path to the OpenAI Codex CLI binary. Default: codex (resolved via PATH).
# Install: npm i -g @openai/codex
# PYANCHOR_CODEX_BIN=codex


# ─── Agent: aider (PYANCHOR_AGENT=aider) ─────────────────────────────

# Path to the aider CLI binary. Default: aider (resolved via PATH).
# Install: pip install aider-chat
# Note: aider expects to operate inside a git repo. If your workspace is not
# a git repo, run `git init` in PYANCHOR_WORKSPACE_DIR once.
# PYANCHOR_AIDER_BIN=aider


# ─── Agent: Google Gemini CLI (PYANCHOR_AGENT=gemini, v0.25.0+) ─────

# Path to the Google Gemini CLI binary. Default: gemini (resolved via PATH).
# Install: npm i -g @google/gemini-cli
# Auth (pick one):
#   - GEMINI_API_KEY=<key from https://aistudio.google.com/apikey>
#   - `gemini auth login` (OAuth, persists in ~/.config/gemini/)
#   - GOOGLE_API_KEY=<key> + GOOGLE_GENAI_USE_VERTEXAI=true (Vertex AI)
# See docs/gemini-setup.md for the full setup walkthrough.
# PYANCHOR_GEMINI_BIN=gemini


# ─── Workspace command overrides (advanced / test-only) ─────────────

# Override the binaries the worker uses to wrap workspace ops. The
# defaults match the production deployment model (sidecar runs as a
# system user, shells out under sudo). Override only in test sandboxes
# (e.g. /bin/true to no-op) or on non-standard distros where sudo /
# flock live elsewhere.
# PYANCHOR_SUDO_BIN=/usr/bin/sudo
# PYANCHOR_FLOCK_BIN=/usr/bin/flock


# ─── Cross-user / file ownership ─────────────────────────────────────

# Owner string for `chown` after the agent writes files back.
# Default: "<currentUser>:<currentUser>"
# PYANCHOR_APP_DIR_OWNER=studio:studio

# pm2 process name (only used by some restart scripts; informational).
# PYANCHOR_FRONTEND_PM2_NAME=


# ─── Timeouts (seconds / milliseconds) ───────────────────────────────

# PYANCHOR_AGENT_TIMEOUT_S=900
# PYANCHOR_INSTALL_TIMEOUT_MS=600000
# PYANCHOR_BUILD_TIMEOUT_MS=900000


# ─── Retention / quotas ──────────────────────────────────────────────

# How many recent messages and activity-log lines to keep in state.json.
# Older entries drop from the head when the limit is exceeded.
# Defaults: 24 messages, 80 log lines (kept the overlay snappy in dev).
# PYANCHOR_MAX_MESSAGES=24
# PYANCHOR_MAX_ACTIVITY_LOG=80

# Max characters accepted in a single user prompt. Express body parser
# already caps at 128KB; this is a semantic cap on top for cost /
# agent-context-window control. POST /api/edit returns 400 above this.
# PYANCHOR_PROMPT_MAX_LENGTH=8000


# ─── Dev ergonomics ──────────────────────────────────────────────────

# When true, skip workspace install + `next build` + frontend restart;
# rsync alone triggers Next.js HMR. Drops the per-edit cycle from
# ~30s-3min to ~1-2s. ONLY safe when the host page is `next dev`-served.
# Sidecar logs a one-line warning at startup when this is enabled.
# Do NOT enable in production.
# PYANCHOR_FAST_RELOAD=false

# When true (legacy v0.1.0 behavior), the worker rm -rf's the workspace
# before every job, forcing a full yarn install + next build each cycle.
# Default (false, since v0.2.3) keeps the workspace persistent so
# node_modules and .next caches survive — yarn install / next build
# become incremental, cutting per-edit time substantially. Flip to true
# only if you suspect stale workspace state is breaking a run.
# PYANCHOR_FRESH_WORKSPACE=false


# ─── Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# PYANCHOR_PORT=3010
# PYANCHOR_HOST=127.0.0.1
# PYANCHOR_RUNTIME_BASE_PATH=/_pyanchor
# PYANCHOR_RUNTIME_ALIAS_PATH=/runtime

# Express trust-proxy preset (default: "loopback").
# Accepts: "loopback" | "linklocal" | "uniquelocal" | "true" | "false"
#       | numeric hop count | comma-separated CIDR list.
# Use "loopback" (default) when pyanchor sits behind nginx on the same
# host. Bump to "uniquelocal" only if you front it from a private LAN
# proxy. Avoid "true" unless you understand the X-Forwarded-* spoof
# implications for IP-based rate limits and `req.secure`.
# PYANCHOR_TRUST_PROXY=loopback

# Accept the deprecated `?token=<...>` query parameter (true) or
# reject it (false, default since v0.2.6). Query tokens leak via
# proxy logs and browser history. Flip on only for legacy callers.
# PYANCHOR_ALLOW_QUERY_TOKEN=false

# CSRF defense: comma-separated origins allowed to call /api/edit and /api/cancel.
# When unset, every origin presenting a valid token is accepted (v0.1.0 behavior).
# When set, requests whose Origin (or Referer) header is not in the list get 403.
# Example: PYANCHOR_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=https://app.example.com,http://localhost:3000
# PYANCHOR_ALLOWED_ORIGINS=


# ─── Paths (auto-derived; override only if needed) ───────────────────

# Directory for state.json and the lock file.
# Default: $HOME/.pyanchor
# PYANCHOR_STATE_DIR=

# Path to a peer process's state file. If set, pyanchor will avoid
# starting a job while the peer process is busy. Useful when another
# tool shares the same app directory.
# PYANCHOR_PEER_STATE_FILE=

# Override only if running pyanchor outside the installed package.
# PYANCHOR_SERVICE_ROOT=
# PYANCHOR_WORKER_SCRIPT=
# PYANCHOR_STATIC_DIR=
# PYANCHOR_APP_DIR_LOCK=


# ─── Output mode / audit log (v0.18.0+) ─────────────────────────────
# How the agent's edits land. apply (default) = rsync → restart.
# pr = open a GitHub PR (requires git + gh setup; see PR mode block).
# dryrun = build only; agent's edits stay in workspace for inspection.
# PYANCHOR_OUTPUT_MODE=apply
# Append-only JSONL log of every job outcome. Off by default.
# Schema documented in src/audit.ts.
# PYANCHOR_AUDIT_LOG=false
# PYANCHOR_AUDIT_LOG_FILE=  # default: <stateDir>/audit.jsonl

# ─── Actor header signing (v0.27.0+, opt-in) ────────────────────────
# When set, X-Pyanchor-Actor must be `<actor>.<hex-sha256-hmac>` —
# values without a valid signature are silently dropped from the
# audit trail (the edit still proceeds; we just don't trust the actor
# field). When unset (default), behavior is unchanged: header value
# is taken at face, capped at 256 chars. Hosts mint header values
# as `<actor>.<hex HMAC-SHA256(secret, actor)>` — pure node:crypto,
# see docs/ACCESS-CONTROL.md for the inline snippet. Generate with:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
# PYANCHOR_ACTOR_SIGNING_SECRET=

# ─── PR mode (v0.19.0+) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used when PYANCHOR_OUTPUT_MODE=pr. Requires:
#   1. Workspace is a git clone of your deployment repo.
#      (`sudo -u <pyanchor user> git clone <remote> $PYANCHOR_WORKSPACE_DIR`)
#   2. `gh auth login` configured for the pyanchor user OR GH_TOKEN env.
# See docs/PRODUCTION-HARDENING.md for the operator setup walkthrough.
# PYANCHOR_GIT_BIN=git
# PYANCHOR_GH_BIN=gh
# PYANCHOR_GIT_REMOTE=origin
# PYANCHOR_GIT_BASE_BRANCH=main
# PYANCHOR_GIT_BRANCH_PREFIX=pyanchor/

# ─── Production gate cookie (v0.17.0+) ──────────────────────────────
# When true, the sidecar refuses every static + API request to anonymous
# traffic (request without the named cookie set). Used in production
# deployments where pyanchor's bootstrap is rendered behind some host-
# side gate (magic-word URL, OAuth, etc.). See docs/SECURITY.md
# recipe B and examples/nextjs-portfolio-gate/.
# PYANCHOR_REQUIRE_GATE_COOKIE=false
# PYANCHOR_GATE_COOKIE_NAME=pyanchor_dev

# ─── Webhooks (v0.20.0+) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# Best-effort POST notifications mirrored from the audit events.
# Empty value = no dispatch for that event. 5s timeout, no retry.
# Format auto-detection: hooks.slack.com → { text }, *.discord.com →
# { content }, anything else → full JSON payload. Override with
# _FORMAT=raw to send the generic payload regardless of host.
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_EDIT_REQUESTED_URL=
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_EDIT_APPLIED_URL=
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_PR_OPENED_URL=
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_EDIT_REQUESTED_FORMAT=auto
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_EDIT_APPLIED_FORMAT=auto
# PYANCHOR_WEBHOOK_PR_OPENED_FORMAT=auto

# ─── Worker IPC (set automatically by the sidecar; do not set manually) ─
# PYANCHOR_JOB_ID
# PYANCHOR_JOB_PROMPT
# PYANCHOR_JOB_TARGET_PATH
# PYANCHOR_JOB_MODE
# PYANCHOR_JOB_ACTOR
# PYANCHOR_STATE_FILE_PATH
# PYANCHOR_RESTART_AFTER_EDIT
